#Approach:

Pascal’s Triangle – nCr Combination Approach

Is problem me hume Pascal Triangle ki rows generate karni hoti hain.
Pascal triangle me har element combination formula se nikal sakte hain:

nCr = n! / (r! * (n-r)!)

Lekin factorial use karenge to time zyada lagega,
isliye hum ek optimized formula use karte hain:

next = previous * (n - i) / i

Yaha:
previous = previous element
i = column index

Har row ka pehla element hamesha 1 hota hai.
Uske baad har next element upar wale formula se generate kar sakte hain.

To approach:
Har row ke liye 1 se start karo
Formula use karke next elements nikaalo
Row ko answer list me add karo
Ye process numRows tak repeat karo

Is approach me factorial calculate nahi karna padta,
aur har row efficiently generate ho jaati hai.

Time Complexity: O(n^2)
Space Complexity: O(1) (excluding output)

#Code:

class Solution {

    private List<Integer> pascal(int n){
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        ans.add(1);
        int x = 1;

        for(int i = 1; i<n; i++){
            x = x * (n-i);
            x = x / (i);
            ans.add(x);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public List<List<Integer>> generate(int numRows) {
        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0; i<numRows; i++){
            result.add(pascal(i+1));
        }
        return result;
    }
}
